NAME - ::<namespace>:: pppox_stats

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

Retrieves statistics for the PPPoX sessions configured on the specified test port or for the PPPoX handle passed in -handle argument.

IxNetwork-NGPF

Retrieves statistics for the PPPoX sessions configured on the specified test port or for the PPPoX handle passed in -handle argument.

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::pppox_stats

List arguments in the alphabetical order or in the reverse alphabetical order.

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

The PPPoX handle for which the PPPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved.When using IxNetwork the statistics will be retrieved for the port where that handle belongs.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

The PPPoX handle for which the PPPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. When using IxNetwork the statistics will be retrieved for the port where that handle belongs.

DEFAULT

 None

-port_handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The port for which the PPPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved.Only available when using IxNetwork to retrieve statistics.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

The port for which the PPPoX sessions statistics needs to be retrieved. Only available when using IxNetwork to retrieve statistics.

DEFAULT

 None

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Specifies statistics retrieval mode as either aggregate for all aggregate - Retrieve statistics for all the sessions.session - Retrieve statistics for each individual session. session_dhcpv6pd - Retrieve dhcp client or dhcp server statistics per session. Available only for IxTclNetwork.session_dhcp_hosts - Retrieve dhcp hosts statistics per session. Available only for IxTclNetwork.session_all - Retrieve all the per session statistics. Available only fot IxTclNetwork

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Specifies statistics retrieval mode as either aggregate for all configured sessions or on a per session basis.

Valid options are:

aggregate

Retrieve statistics for all the sessions.

session

Retrieve statistics for each individual session.

session_dhcpv6pd

Retrieve dhcp client or dhcp server statistics per session. Available only for IxTclNetwork.

session_dhcp_hosts

Retrieve dhcp hosts statistics per session.Available only for IxTclNetwork.

session_all

Retrieve all the per session statistics. Available only fot IxTclNetwork

DEFAULT

 None

-source

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

Valid only when a port handle is available

Valid options are:

client

indicates to retrieve client specific statistics

server

indicates to retrieve server specific statistics

DEFAULT

 None

-csv_filename

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The .csv filename that can be created under HLT library install folder and where per session stats can be found.Only available when using IxAccess to retrieve statistics. Not available when using IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

 Not supported

-retry

Supported platforms Details

-execution_timeout

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This is the timeout for the function. The setting is in seconds. Setting this setting to 60 it will mean that the command must complete in under 60 seconds. If the command will last more than 60 seconds the command will be terminated by force. This flag can be used to prevent dead locks occuring in IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

1800

RETURN VALUES

Supported Platform Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

status

$::SUCCESS | $::FAILURE

log

If status is failure, detailed information provided.

AGGREGATE STATS

The stats can be used with or without <port_handle>

PER RANGE STATS

If -handle is specified, the aggregate.* keys that are not prefixed are the pppox per range statistics. If more than one handle is specified, the per range statistics will be prefixed with the handle value. If -handle is not provided, the perRange statistics are not returned.

PER RANGE STATS

The aggregate statistic keys that are not documented as having a 'pppox_handle' prefix will always have the 'N/A' value.

PER RANGE STATS

Aggregate per port statistics will also be returned for the ports on which the pppox handles reside

NOTES

IxNetwork-NGPF

Coded versus functional specification. 1) Session ID will be PPPoE session ID for the case of PPPoE and PPPoEoA. For the case of PPPoA, session ID will be VPI/VCI. 2) Per session stats retrieval can take long time. 3) Following stats have not been implemented yet: aggregate.disconnecting aggregate.atm_mode aggregate.connect_attempts aggregate.disconnect_success aggregate.sessions_down aggregate.disconnect_failed 4) PPPoX implementation using IxTclAccess is NOT SUPPORTED starting from HLTAPI 3.30.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

Coded versus functional specification.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

1) Session ID will be PPPoE session ID for the case of PPPoE and PPPoEoA. For the case of PPPoA, session ID will be VPI/VCI.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

2) Per session stats retrieval can take long time.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

3) Following stats have not been implemented yet:aggregate.disconnectingaggregate.atm_modeaggregate.connect_attemptsaggregate.disconnect_successaggregate.sessions_downaggregate.disconnect_failed4) PPPoX implementation using IxTclAccess is NOT SUPPORTED starting from HLTAPI 3.30.

NAME - <namespace>::pppox_stats

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

Retrieves statistics for the PPPoX sessions configured on the specified test port or for the PPPoX handle passed in -handle argument.

IxNetwork-NGPF

Retrieves statistics for the PPPoX sessions configured on the specified test port or for the PPPoX handle passed in -handle argument.

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Specifies statistics retrieval mode as either aggregate for all aggregate - Retrieve statistics for all the sessions.session - Retrieve statistics for each individual session. session_dhcpv6pd - Retrieve dhcp client or dhcp server statistics per session. Available only for IxTclNetwork.session_dhcp_hosts - Retrieve dhcp hosts statistics per session. Available only for IxTclNetwork.session_all - Retrieve all the per session statistics. Available only fot IxTclNetwork

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Specifies statistics retrieval mode as either aggregate for all configured sessions or on a per session basis.

Valid options are:

aggregate

Retrieve statistics for all the sessions.

session

Retrieve statistics for each individual session.

session_dhcpv6pd

Retrieve dhcp client or dhcp server statistics per session. Available only for IxTclNetwork.

session_dhcp_hosts

Retrieve dhcp hosts statistics per session.Available only for IxTclNetwork.

session_all

Retrieve all the per session statistics. Available only fot IxTclNetwork

DEFAULT

 None

Supported platforms Details

execution_timeout

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This is the timeout for the function. The setting is in seconds. Setting this setting to 60 it will mean that the command must complete in under 60 seconds. If the command will last more than 60 seconds the command will be terminated by force. This flag can be used to prevent dead locks occuring in IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

1800

AGGREGATE STATS

The stats can be used with or without <port_handle>

PER RANGE STATS

If -handle is specified, the aggregate.* keys that are not prefixed are the pppox per range statistics. If more than one handle is specified, the per range statistics will be prefixed with the handle value. If -handle is not provided, the perRange statistics are not returned.

PER RANGE STATS

The aggregate statistic keys that are not documented as having a 'pppox_handle' prefix will always have the 'N/A' value.

PER RANGE STATS

Aggregate per port statistics will also be returned for the ports on which the pppox handles reside

NOTES

IxNetwork-NGPF

Coded versus functional specification. 1) Session ID will be PPPoE session ID for the case of PPPoE and PPPoEoA. For the case of PPPoA, session ID will be VPI/VCI. 2) Per session stats retrieval can take long time. 3) Following stats have not been implemented yet: aggregate.disconnecting aggregate.atm_mode aggregate.connect_attempts aggregate.disconnect_success aggregate.sessions_down aggregate.disconnect_failed 4) PPPoX implementation using IxTclAccess is NOT SUPPORTED starting from HLTAPI 3.30.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

Coded versus functional specification.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

1) Session ID will be PPPoE session ID for the case of PPPoE and PPPoEoA. For the case of PPPoA, session ID will be VPI/VCI.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

2) Per session stats retrieval can take long time.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

3) Following stats have not been implemented yet:aggregate.disconnectingaggregate.atm_modeaggregate.connect_attemptsaggregate.disconnect_successaggregate.sessions_downaggregate.disconnect_failed4) PPPoX implementation using IxTclAccess is NOT SUPPORTED starting from HLTAPI 3.30.

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Specifies statistics retrieval mode as either aggregate for all configured sessions or on a per session basis.

Valid options are:

aggregate

Retrieve statistics for all the sessions.

session

Retrieve statistics for each individual session.

session_dhcpv6pd

Retrieve dhcp client or dhcp server statistics per session. Available only for IxTclNetwork.

session_dhcp_hosts

Retrieve dhcp hosts statistics per session.Available only for IxTclNetwork.

session_all

Retrieve all the per session statistics. Available only fot IxTclNetwork

DEFAULT

 None

source

client

indicates to retrieve client specific statistics

server

execution_timeout

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This is the timeout for the function. The setting is in seconds. Setting this setting to 60 it will mean that the command must complete in under 60 seconds. If the command will last more than 60 seconds the command will be terminated by force. This flag can be used to prevent dead locks occuring in IxNetwork.

DEFAULT

1800

The stats can be used with or without <port_handle>

PER RANGE STATS

If -handle is specified, the aggregate.* keys that are not prefixed are the pppox per range statistics. If more than one handle is specified, the per range statistics will be prefixed with the handle value. If -handle is not provided, the perRange statistics are not returned.

PER RANGE STATS

The aggregate statistic keys that are not documented as having a 'pppox_handle' prefix will always have the 'N/A' value.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

AGGREGATE STATS

The stats can be used with or without <port_handle>

PER RANGE STATS

If -handle is specified, the aggregate.* keys that are not prefixed are the pppox per range statistics. If more than one handle is specified, the per range statistics will be prefixed with the handle value. If -handle is not provided, the perRange statistics are not returned.

PER RANGE STATS

The aggregate statistic keys that are not documented as having a 'pppox_handle' prefix will always have the 'N/A' value.

PER RANGE STATS

Aggregate per port statistics will also be returned for the ports on which the pppox handles reside

NOTES

IxNetwork-NGPF

Coded versus functional specification. 1) Session ID will be PPPoE session ID for the case of PPPoE and PPPoEoA. For the case of PPPoA, session ID will be VPI/VCI. 2) Per session stats retrieval can take long time. 3) Following stats have not been implemented yet: aggregate.disconnecting aggregate.atm_mode aggregate.connect_attempts aggregate.disconnect_success aggregate.sessions_down aggregate.disconnect_failed 4) PPPoX implementation using IxTclAccess is NOT SUPPORTED starting from HLTAPI 3.30.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

Coded versus functional specification.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

1) Session ID will be PPPoE session ID for the case of PPPoE and PPPoEoA. For the case of PPPoA, session ID will be VPI/VCI.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

2) Per session stats retrieval can take long time.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

3) Following stats have not been implemented yet:aggregate.disconnectingaggregate.atm_modeaggregate.connect_attemptsaggregate.disconnect_successaggregate.sessions_downaggregate.disconnect_failed4) PPPoX implementation using IxTclAccess is NOT SUPPORTED starting from HLTAPI 3.30.
